headline: Frontend Software Engineer | React | Next.js | Vue | Nuxt.js | Cypress | Playwright | Jest/Vitest | Write code | Test code | Refactor with confidence | Ship with confidence
summary:
I am a full-time software developer, working in web development for more than four years. Mostly work with React, Next.js,  Vue, and Nuxt.js.
Experience in starting a project from scratch and maintaining & improving existing projects.
Capable of working in a team and independently.

experiences.title: Full Stack Developer
experiences.description:
Migration and Improvements of Geriatrie Project: The project aims to migrate “Geriatrie Pepper” web app into Geriatrie android application with some improvements in design. And decoupling “Geriatrie Admin” from a pepper robot platform and rewriting of “Geriatrie Admin” web app into Geriatrie Content Management System (CMS) by making responsive design and improving designs. 
The project uses the following technologies.
1.	Android Studio with kotlin language to develop an android application
2.	Google Material Design Components
3.	Frontend framework Vue.js with Vuetify.js (design components library) to build an interactive user interface for CMS
4.	Firebase as an application backend
5.	Google Cloud Platform
6.	Bit cloud to share the common user interface components across projects
7.	Jira Software and Confluence as the project management tool

experiences.title: Full Stack Developer
experiences.description:
Health care, Maxima Medisch Centrum (MMC) wants to put the social humanoid robot "Pepper" into their working environment to solve the problems of elderly people being frustrated during the stay in health care and their care professionals were not able to be with the patients more time to make them engaged.  
Therefore, an assignment was to develop a web-based application for pepper robot which helps them to keep their patients (especially old people) entertained and engaged during the stay in health care by introducing pepper robot onto their working environment. The pepper will be a colleague of the health care professional and work with them together.

experiences.title: Frontend and Backend Developer (PROEP- Distrubted System)
experiences.description: The project aims at developing a distributed system for an organization of a restaurant which solves the problem of the restaurant such as managing their inventory and their employee's work schedule. The system consists of a desktop application (WPF) which is used by an inventory manager to update the stock, employees use to clock in/out and view their work schedule when they don`t have a mobile with them, mobile application (android) to clock in/out at work and view their work schedule and centrally hosted service (WCF) which manages request from those applications. During the project, we make use of Core Dot Net Framework library as well as popular framework MVVMCross5
